By default all newly created buckets are PRIVATE. Yow can set up access control to your buckets useing;
- Bucket Policies
- Access Control Lists

S3 buckets can be configured to create access logs which log all requests made to the S3 bucket.
This can be sent to another bucket and even another bucket in another account.

Encryption in Transit is achieved by
- SSL/TLS
Encryption at rest is achieved by 
on the server side:
- S3 managed keys - SSE-S3
- AWS Key management service, Managed keys - SSE-KMS
- Server side encryption with Customer provided Keys - SSE-C
on the client side the file is encrypted and uploaded:
